================
description
================

1) This program accept file name from user, which contains data of all files
 (file which created by previous program). We have to print all file names whose size
 is greater that 10 bytes.
2) Required file name will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	file name [example: "allCombine" (regular) file.]
	output	:	result - file name having size greater than 10 byte.
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p="parameter_value" 
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1)If the given file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
